From be1110cf680222f679aa4375b24aa620fc0f6bce Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Gautham Kumar Senthilkumaran <gauthamk@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Sep 2025 15:22:19 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:CP: wifi:ath12k: Fix arvif stale entry in ahvif for
 legacy repeater

In legacy repeater mode, arvif is assigned to ahvif during
channel context assignment when connecting to a root AP.
This is expected, as legacy repeaters maintain entries in
both deflink and link ID 0.

However, arvif is currently removed only during link change operations,
leading to stale entries in ahvif after disconnection. Since mac80211
does not track this link, it must be explicitly removed during
channel context unassignment.

Fix this by adding arvif cleanup during channel context unassignment for
legacy repeaters. MLO-capable repeaters continue to rely on link change
operations for link management. This ensures arvif is properly cleared on
disconnection from the root AP.

Patch-dependency: None

Signed-off-by: Gautham Kumar Senthilkumaran <gauthamk@qti.qualcomm.com>

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
index 06e87d4..21b9fd2 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
@@ -18518,6 +18518,19 @@ ath12k_mac_unassign_vif_chanctx_handle(struct ieee80211_hw *hw,
 		reinit_completion(&ar->completed_11d_scan);
 		ar->state_11d = ATH12K_11D_PREPARING;
 	}
+
+	/* In legacy station association with the AP,
+	 * arvif is created during channel context assignment.
+	 * However, since mac80211 is unaware of this link,
+	 * it is not deleted automatically. To prevent stale arvif
+	 * entries in ahvif, this link must be explicitly removed
+	 * during channel context unassignment.
+	 */
+	if (!vif->valid_links) {
+		ath12k_mac_remove_link_interface(hw, arvif);
+		ath12k_mac_unassign_link_vif(arvif);
+	}
+
 }
 
 static void
